From bef29818c83aa579ac28cedb507610ab5f2ac39a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 21 Aug 2025 22:33:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:wifi:ath12k: Remove power mode assignment in
 ath12k_mac_fill_reg_tpc_info

Remove the assignment of power mode in ath12k_mac_fill_reg_tpc_info
as this is introduced as part of a WAR in
win.wlan_host_opensource.1.0.

Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Patch-dependency: 0320-wifi-ath12k-Fix-the-crash-during-associate-6G-slo.patch

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 6 ++----
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index 3cc3855..d992eb3 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -9002,10 +9002,8 @@ void ath12k_mac_fill_reg_tpc_info(struct ath12k *ar,
 	}
 
 	reg_6g_power_mode = bss_conf->power_type;
-	if (reg_6g_power_mode == IEEE80211_REG_UNSET_AP)
-		reg_6g_power_mode = IEEE80211_REG_LPI_AP;
-	else if (reg_6g_power_mode == IEEE80211_REG_SP_AP &&
-		 !ar->afc.is_6ghz_afc_power_event_received)
+	if (reg_6g_power_mode == IEEE80211_REG_SP_AP &&
+	    !ar->afc.is_6ghz_afc_power_event_received)
 		reg_6g_power_mode = NL80211_REG_REGULAR_CLIENT_SP + 1;
 
         chan = ctx->def.chan;
-- 
